1200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20antiquated%20kurma%20ghar%20concept%20involves%20women%20living%20in%20a%20mud%20hut%20for%20the%20duration%20of%20their%20menstrual%20cycle%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fhealthcare-access-in-tribal-areas-1-1728467626.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fhealthcare-access-in-tribal-areas-1-1728467626-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fhealthcare-access-in-tribal-areas-1-1728467626-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fhealthcare-access-in-tribal-areas-1-1728467626-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fhealthcare-access-in-tribal-areas-1-1728467626-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-369358%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20antiquated%20%3Cem%3Ekurma%20ghar%3C%2Fem%3E%20concept%20involves%20women%20living%20in%20a%20mud%20hut%20for%20the%20duration%20of%20their%20menstrual%20cycle.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithin%20the%20hut%2C%20their%20stock%20of%20period%20cloths%20was%20bait%20for%20lizards%20and%20mice.%20And%20god%20forbid%20the%20women%20run%20out%20of%20pads%2C%20they%20were%20at%20the%20mercy%20of%20nature.%20Sometimes%20%3Cem%3Emahua%20%3C%2Fem%3E(a%20tropical%20Indian%20tree)%20leaves%20covered%20in%20paddy%20chaff%20served%20the%20purpose%3B%20other%20times%20banana%20leaves%20helped%20soak%20the%20blood.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20what%20really%20amused%20Dr%20Rani%20was%20the%20fervour%20with%20which%20the%20women%20regarded%20the%20system.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20told%20me%20that%20they%20liked%20the%20days%20they%20spent%20at%20the%20%3Cem%3Ekurma%20ghar%3C%2Fem%3E%20because%20it%20was%20a%20chance%20to%20rest.%20It%20was%20one%20of%20the%20few%20opportunities